[SN]TITLE[SN]
Internet troll jailed over tweets to Leanne Wood

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An internet troll has been jailed for 12 weeks for offensive comments posted on Twitter to Plaid Cymru leader Leanne Wood.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
David Begley, 47, from Gorseinon, Swansea, made references to rape in messages to Ms Wood as she appeared on a TV debate about the referendum.
Begley, a music promoter and DJ, admitted sending a communication conveying an offensive message.
He was sentenced at Swansea Magistrates' Court.
Ms Wood represented the Remain campaign in debates during the build-up to the referendum vote.
Stephen Harrett, defending, said: "He sent the message on the spur of the moment."
